Program: Discovery
Title: The DNA family tree
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwvz
Last Broadcast Date: 07 April 1997
How DNA analysis is showing just how closely related we are to apes. Also in the programme, why cancer is so uncommon, evidence that at least one of Jupiter's moons could support life and a vaccine for bananas. Presenter: Martin Redfern.